c-shquote - POSIX Shell Compatible Argument Parser in Standard ISO-C11

ABOUT:
        The c-shquote project is a standalone implementation of POSIX Shell
        compatible argumnet parsing written in Standard ISO-C11.

        To use shquote, include c-shquote.h and link to the libcshquote.so
        library. A pkg-config entry is provided as well.

        For API documentation, see the c-shquote.h header file, as well as the
        docbook comments for each function.

DETAILS:
        https://github.com/c-util/c-shquote/wiki

BUG REPORTS:
        https://github.com/c-util/c-shquote/issues

GIT:
        git@github.com:c-util/c-shquote.git
        https://github.com/c-util/c-shquote.git

GITWEB:
        https://github.com/c-util/c-shquote

LICENSE:
        Apache Software License 2.0 (LICENSE)
        See COPYING for details.

REQUIREMENTS:
        The requirements for c-shquote are:

            libc (e.g., glibc >= 2.16)

        At build-time, the following software is required:

            meson >= 0.41
            pkg-config >= 0.29

INSTALL:
        The meson build-system is used for c-shquote. Contact upstream
        documentation for detailed help. In most situations the following
        commands are sufficient to build and install c-shquote from source:

            $ mkdir build
            $ cd build
            $ meson setup . ..
            $ ninja
            $ ninja test
            # ninja install

        No custom configuration options are available.
